{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh noodles in it. Cover with boiling water and cook as per packet instructions.","Place oil, ginger and spring onions\/shallots into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add tamari sauce, fish sauce, honey and juice of 1 lime and cook <nobr>5 min\/100°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>, <strong>without measuring cup<\/strong>.","Line a plate with paper towel and set aside. Place a large frying pan over medium-high heat and add oil. Place cornflour, flour, salt and Sichuan pepper into a snaplock bag. Add fish and toss to coat. Working in batches, fry fish for 3-4 minutes on each side, until golden and cooked through. Transfer onto prepared plate to drain.","Drain reserved noodles using Varoma dish and transfer back into thermal serving bowl. Pour over ginger lime sauce and toss to combine. Cover and keep warm.","Place pea shoots, coriander and Thai basil (optional) into a bowl and toss to combine. Divide reserved noodles between serving bowls and top with fish. Garnish with herb salad and serve with lime wedges."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["200 - 250 g dried egg noodles","boiling water, for soaking","15 g sesame oil","3 cm piece fresh ginger, peeled","3 spring onions\/shallots, trimmed and cut into halves","50 g tamari sauce","10 g fish sauce","60 g honey","2 limes, juice only, 1 cut into wedges, to serve","oil (approx. 200 g), for frying","2 tbsp cornflour","2 tbsp plain flour","1 tsp salt","¼ tsp Sichuan pepper (see Tips)","4 boneless white fish fillets, cut into pieces (6 cm - see Tips)","pea shoots, trimmed, to serve","fresh coriander leaves, to serve","fresh Thai basil leaves, to serve (optional)"]}],"id":"r256229","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-jFY4u9zjagw\/XZQvE-WqVjI\/AAAAAAAAcZ4\/BW16tlUjzfI2FE_lqo77CaBK9eCbDBVbwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_BN5ojYEz7X5rNA2O.png","title":"Fish with ginger lime sauce","publishedAt":"2018-10-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"35.8 g","fat":"57.1 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"67.6 g","calories":"3893.8 kJ \/ 927.1 kcal"},"usefulItems":"thermal serving bowl or other large bowl, plate, paper towel, snaplock bag, large frying pan, bowl, serving bowls, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["You can find Sichuan pepper at most major supermarkets and Asian food stores. Otherwise, you can replace it with ground black pepper.","For the best result, we recommend using fresh fish fillets. Cooking times may vary according to type and thickness of fillets. To save time you can start preparing fish while the sauce is cooking."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","35m","4 portions"]}